  "title": "Butchers / Senior Butchers",
  "description": "<p>The butcher provides various services such as, but not limited to, weighing, wrapping, cutting, and trimming meat from larger wholesale portions in a retail or factory environment.<br /></p><p><u><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></u></p><p>- Upon goods receiving, inspect and ensure meat is at the correct temperature and condition before storage</p><p>- Ensure that meat handling and storage procedures comply with hygiene and safety standards</p><p>- Operate and perform meat-cutting functions including trimming, deboning, portioning, slicing, and processing to specifications</p><p>- Ensure that meat processing equipment is in clean and good working conditions</p><p>- Maintain an organised and sanitary work environment</p><p>- Record sampling, wastage, and daily production/sales</p><p>- Prepare sales transactions</p><p>- Provide service to customers, meeting their needs and expectations</p><p>- Execute other ad-hoc duties, as required<br /></p><p><u><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></u></p><p>- Basic literacy in English language</p><p>- Minimum 3 years of work experience in food- or butchery-related industry</p><ul><li>WSQ certification in basic food hygiene</li><li>Ability to work in cold room environment (Retail)</li></ul>",
